OL,3,CUnmasking the monster: Reclaiming a
OL,4,Cmother's truth from a father's lie
OL,6,FBut also the sense of relief as he'd
OL,7,Fgrown up feeling abandoned by his
OL,8,Fmother. The false narrative that she
OL,9,Fhad died by suicide and on his
OL,10,Fbirthday had been dispelled.
OL,12,FNow he knew, he said, she had never
OL,13,Fwanted to leave her children.
OL,15,FHazel Stewart has tried three times to
OL,16,Fappeal her sentence but Seamus doesn't
OL,17,F'buy into' Stewart's narrative of
OL,18,Fcoercive control and urged her to just
OL,19,F'say sorry'.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/11
