OL,3,CUnmasking the monster: Reclaiming a
OL,4,Cmother's truth from a father's lie
OL,6,FAs for his father Seamus said he
OL,7,F'aspires to forgive him' one day.
OL,9,FHe doesn't wish him harm instead and
OL,10,Fmagnanimously wishes him: 'happiness,
OL,11,Fhonesty - with himself and humility'.
OL,12,F'It's a long wish list I know,' he
OL,13,Ftold me.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/11
